OL,3,CThousands lose NHS healthcare funding
OL,4,Cafter living 'longer than expected'
OL,6,FOf these, 1,170 people were deemed no
OL,7,Flonger eligible for CHC funding, 756
OL,8,Fremained eligible and others were
OL,9,Fgiven NHS nursing care funding at a
OL,10,Flower rate.
OL,12,FIn Tees Valley, there were 3,170 fast-
OL,13,Ftrack reviews, of which 1,096 were
OL,14,Fdeemed no longer eligible and 1,350
OL,15,Fremained eligible.
OL,17,FIn Cheshire and Merseyside from July
OL,18,F2022 to December 2023, some 774 people
OL,19,Freceiving fast-track funding had their
OL,20,Fcase reviewed, of whom 172 were deemed
OL,21,Fno longer eligible for funding.
